<subSubSection id="C6A0ECEFA525FFC3FF64FED9FD6EAD76" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8E05BF64A525FFC3FF64FED9FD6EAD76" blockId="33.[151,1437,152,756]" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">
<emphasis id="BCCE6376A525FFC3FF64FED9FE85AD2A" bold="true" box="[199,334,261,287]" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Etymology.</emphasis>
The epithet is a noun in the genitive case, in honor of Luis Alberto Pereira, who is one of the greatest specialists in Neotropical 
<taxonomicName id="49BAC4E7A525FFC3FE7CFEF5FD6AAD76" authorityName="Pocock" authorityYear="1895" box="[479,673,297,323]" class="Chilopoda" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Geophilomorpha" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="order">Geophilomorpha</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C6A0ECEFA525FFC3FF64FE90FC3AAB32" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8E05BF64A525FFC3FF64FE90FCBFAE9E" blockId="33.[151,1437,152,756]" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">
<emphasis id="BCCE6376A525FFC3FF64FE90FE89AD52" bold="true" box="[199,322,332,359]" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
A species of 
<taxonomicName id="49BAC4E7A525FFC3FE40FE91FD93AD52" box="[483,600,333,359]" class="Chilopoda" family="Aphilodontidae" genus="Aphilodon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Geophilomorpha" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="BCCE6376A525FFC3FE40FE91FD93AD52" box="[483,600,333,359]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Aphilodon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with: around 73–77 leg-bearing segments; known body length in adults 
<quantity id="49421281A525FFC3FF34FEADFEDFADBE" box="[151,276,369,395]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.7" metricValueMax="7.1" metricValueMin="2.3" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" unit="mm" value="47.0" valueMax="71.0" valueMin="23.0">23–71 mm</quantity>
; cephalic plate length/width ratio 1.3–1.4; antenna ca. 2.3-2.7 times as long as cephalic plate; pectinate lamella of mandible with curved denticles; coxosternite of second maxillae not distinctly shorter in middle part; telopodite of second maxillae with article 3 shorter than article 2, with 1–4 setae in apical or subapical position and a sensillum in subapical position; forcipular pretergite exposed; forcipule with lateral margin posteriorly straight; tarsungulum ca. 0.9 times as long as trochanteroprefemur+femur; forcipule with 3+1 denticles; distal denticle of trochanteroprefemur, denticle of femur and denticle of tibia relatively large and denticle of tarsungulum relatively small; all pleurites conspicuous; each coxopleuron with 22–44 coxal pores in adults, all sparse; ultimate presternite not visible; metasternite of ultimate leg-bearing segment length/width ratio ca. 0.7–0.8; ultimate legs ca. 1.5 times as long as penultimate legs, tarsus 1 ca. 1.2 times as long as tibia.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8E05BF64A525FFC3FF64FD69FBF2AEC1" blockId="33.[151,1437,152,756]" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">
<taxonomicName id="49BAC4E7A525FFC3FF64FD69FE89AEFA" authority="Calvanese &amp; Brescovit &amp; Bonato, 2019" authorityName="Calvanese &amp; Brescovit &amp; Bonato" authorityYear="2019" box="[199,322,693,719]" class="Chilopoda" family="Aphilodontidae" genus="Aphilodon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Geophilomorpha" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pereirai" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis id="BCCE6376A525FFC3FF64FD69FE89AEFA" box="[199,322,693,719]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">A. pereirai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="BCCE6376A525FFC3FEEFFD69FE45AEFA" bold="true" box="[332,398,693,719]" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A7FDDE0DA525FFC3FEEFFD69FE45AEFA" box="[332,398,693,719]" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
differs from all other species of 
<taxonomicName id="49BAC4E7A525FFC3FCB2FD69FC4DAEFA" box="[785,902,693,719]" class="Chilopoda" family="Aphilodontidae" genus="Aphilodon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Geophilomorpha" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="BCCE6376A525FFC3FCB2FD69FC4DAEFA" box="[785,902,693,719]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Aphilodon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by having pectinate lamella of mandible with curved denticles (
<figureCitation id="1681A3E1A525FFC3FEFEFD05FE65AEC6" box="[349,430,728,755]" captionStart="FIGURE 25" captionStartId="33.[151,250,1594,1619]" captionTargetBox="[158,1430,774,1568]" captionTargetId="figure@33.[151,1436,769,1574]" captionTargetPageId="33" captionText="FIGURE 25. A–E, Aphilodon pereirai n. sp. Female paratype (IBSP 3784): A, mandibles, dorsal; B, pectinate lamella of left mandible, dorsal; C, apex of article 3 of the left telopodite of second maxillae, lateral; D, denticles of right forcipule, ventral; E, terminal part of body, ventral. Abbreviations: MTL: metasternite of ultimate leg-bearing segment. Scale bars: 0.1 (A, D–E), 0.03 (B–C) mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3542929" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3542929/files/figure.png" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Fig. 25</figureCitation>
A–B) and ultimate presternite not visible (
<figureCitation id="1681A3E1A525FFC3FC25FD05FC24AEC6" box="[902,1007,728,755]" captionStart="FIGURE 25" captionStartId="33.[151,250,1594,1619]" captionTargetBox="[158,1430,774,1568]" captionTargetId="figure@33.[151,1436,769,1574]" captionTargetPageId="33" captionText="FIGURE 25. A–E, Aphilodon pereirai n. sp. Female paratype (IBSP 3784): A, mandibles, dorsal; B, pectinate lamella of left mandible, dorsal; C, apex of article 3 of the left telopodite of second maxillae, lateral; D, denticles of right forcipule, ventral; E, terminal part of body, ventral. Abbreviations: MTL: metasternite of ultimate leg-bearing segment. Scale bars: 0.1 (A, D–E), 0.03 (B–C) mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3542929" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3542929/files/figure.png" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Figs 25E</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="1681A3E1A525FFC3FC59FD05FBE7AEC1" box="[1018,1068,729,756]" captionStart="FIGURE 26" captionStartId="34.[151,250,1678,1703]" captionTargetBox="[159,1430,1025,1654]" captionTargetId="figure@34.[151,1437,1021,1658]" captionTargetPageId="34" captionText="FIGURE 26. A–E, Aphilodon pereirai n. sp. Female paratype (IBSP 3784): A, habitus, ventral. Male paratype (IBSP 3784): B, anterior part of body, dorsal; C, same, ventral; D, terminal part of body, dorsal; E, same, ventral. Scale bars: 1 mm (A–E)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3542931" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3542931/files/figure.png" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">26E</figureCitation>
);
</paragraph>
